<paragraph blockId="74.[151,1437,1228,2009]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis: Cross-vein R-M just before middle of discal cell. ST8 with a groove dorsally, no m.a. Surstyli asymmetrical, both with basal lobes ventrally; epandrium wider than long; SES with 12–13 hairs on both sides; phallic guide broad, inner surface curved, tip may be broken.</paragraph>
